 <li>Jurdi, Rozzet, H., Hage, S., Chow, Henry P.H., (2011). &nbsp;<a href="http://journals.sfu.ca/cjhe/index.php/cjhe/article/view/1/2304">Academic Dishonesty in the Canadian Classroom: Behaviours of a Sample of University Students<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>. Canadian Journal of Higher Education, 41 (3), 1-35.</li> 
 <li>Lawson, A.E., Lewis Jr., C.M., &amp; Birk, J.P. (1999). Why do students “cook” data? Journal of College Teaching, 29(3), 191-198.</li> 
 <li>Oxford Brookes University. (2005). <a href="http://www.brookes.ac.uk/services/ocsld/resources/plagiarism.html">Deterring, detecting and dealing with plagiarism<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>.</li> 
 <li>Wilkinson, S. (2003). Keeping students from cutting corners. CENEAR, 81 (15), 51-52.</li> 
 <li>York University. (2005). <a href="http://teachingcommons.yorku.ca/resources-2/teaching-strategies/academic-integrity/academic-dishonesty-in-laboratory-environments">Academic dishonesty in laboratory environments<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>.</li> 
